      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 3,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"injected_lesson_block\": \"Known failure modes to verify before claiming\\nThese are advisory lessons from previous supervisor runs. They do not satisfy any gate by themselves.\\nUse them as a checklist only: do not block, revise, deny, or accept solely because a lesson exists. A step-repetition lesson applies only when current evidence proves the same handoff, artifacts, and source state are being repeated.\\n1. [deliverable_evidence_failed] unknown (source_run_id=vela2-prod-confidence-001): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n2. [missing_worker_signal] worker_invocation (source_run_id=cffe55b8-47b9-4cc0-b025-586aeb0ee5e9): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n3. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\\n4. [FM-1.3] Step repetition (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Change the plan or evidence before retrying; do not repeat the same handoff.\\n5. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=f89bc699-1b4e-4713-95b7-d1493a3acfd8): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\",\n  \"injected_lesson_block_sha256\": \"829d220b66bab5c228dc13757a33b6417eba638735b26fcdd3b6bfd95aa9e2c7\",\n  \"injected_lesson_ids\": [\n    \"lesson-59913963cdfc567d8fe610e82aee863ebb77307f753f7046210498c8c522c5e7\",\n    \"lesson-6e3b08262245b3eade5743e9ddb1a92bfb42a34ec49e8b4f2b0792ca1834a590\",\n    \"lesson-833931ec30fbdcacaef5c7df91fae73a71b7ac537110ccf9cab2ec2e80ec6a52\",\n    \"lesson-cd61385380aa0d71d9927ec5c8f719f315a9191aaf387fdc93862d0a6d71f1ef\",\n    \"lesson-715f39df8c3dc22bea09092f80685d87f086d8cdbbf58a0ec008ce0e27d1cb38\"\n  ],\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nGrow the oracle-isolated mergeability corpus with held-out reporting and no-regression controls for true-positive solved cases.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\\n\\nRuntime TDD test contract:\\nThe supervisor runtime floor will verify that every TDD-named test below appears in supervisor-generated runtime evidence. Include tests/commands covering all of them in outcome.tests. Explicitly skipped tests must carry a recorded pytest skip reason; silently absent tests block the gate.\\nUse only canonical gate decisions (`accept`, `revise`, or `deny`). Do not return `accept_with_residual`; if test execution needs verification, declare the exact pytest commands/nodeids and let the supervisor runtime floor rerun them.\\nIf the Claude Bash/test tool is unavailable but the implementation diff is complete, do not block solely on that local tooling outage. Return `accept` with test_status=`unknown`, list the exact pytest commands/nodeids, and make no tests-passed claim; the supervisor runtime floor is the authority and will block the gate on failing or missing tests.\\n- test_validate_mergeability_corpus_rejects_task_without_positive_control\\n- test_validate_mergeability_corpus_rejects_task_without_negative_control\\n- test_validate_mergeability_corpus_rejects_task_without_false_accept_trap\\n- test_paired_report_separates_heldout_metrics_and_confidence_intervals\\n- test_no_regression_blocks_prior_true_positive_rejects_not_false_accepts\\n- test_heldout_no_regression_report_remains_non_applyable\\n- test_best_of_k_peak_cannot_be_labeled_heldout_improvement\\n\\nKnown failure modes to verify before claiming\\nThese are advisory lessons from previous supervisor runs. They do not satisfy any gate by themselves.\\nUse them as a checklist only: do not block, revise, deny, or accept solely because a lesson exists. A step-repetition lesson applies only when current evidence proves the same handoff, artifacts, and source state are being repeated.\\n1. [deliverable_evidence_failed] unknown (source_run_id=vela2-prod-confidence-001): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n2. [missing_worker_signal] worker_invocation (source_run_id=cffe55b8-47b9-4cc0-b025-586aeb0ee5e9): Verify this known failure mode explicitly before claiming the gate is complete.\\n3. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\\n4. [FM-1.3] Step repetition (source_run_id=8ebdbc89-0185-4962-be6f-b0f593887670): Change the plan or evidence before retrying; do not repeat the same handoff.\\n5. [FM-2.4] Information withholding (source_run_id=f89bc699-1b4e-4713-95b7-d1493a3acfd8): Address independent reviewer objections with concrete evidence references.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-heldout-corpus-noregression-20260619/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"9600ade108f16ca110b5656bea557fead02bcfb23ba274988063b8a9f982e18f\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-heldout-corpus-noregression-20260619/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"a8baf0ff77529f0a9d16a8a02c5bdc3ee8f7184970a9f749ae6465302e61e7ac\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-heldout-corpus-noregression-20260619/source/issues.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"c20afea98ad445125dc43f11eacf5343d562819733911377881cc2ee4c362e7f\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"tdd_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-heldout-corpus-noregression-20260619/source/tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"3963075f3acceb6c8ba33d20a84d6c45a3aeb2e06ea839312fa07e487ffbeefc\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-heldout-corpus-noregression-20260619/source/grill-findings-tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"9dc224302637f0c3ff9745d79ca0a1f8902f67f9e9c17f6870be6227e80b6af6\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"implementation_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-heldout-corpus-noregression-20260619/source/implementation-plan.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"1c556f1a47f86cdf0ab4f7a888d2f5b5a4c75a20b397f3c4601a1b265f8b3bd9\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/mergeability-heldout-corpus-noregression-20260619/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"3c8acca77e886aa2f8e792b8ce9bf712ad7ef255e0ff80dd9cadfdbb1e291042\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"k